How to choose mattress and mattress: women and men look for different things
Nothing of a pompous frame for the bed; what really confers its quality to a good bed is the surface to lie down, that is, the mattress and the sommer.
First of all, they must be complemented to perfection so that they can be adapted to specific users.
During the election numerous elements come into play, including the weight, height, state of health and sex of the owner.
It is also important the type of interior in which the mattress and the sommer are located.
A typical example?
For example, in a weekend cabin that does not usually have heating, latex mattresses should not be used because they are "heated" more slowly.
In addition, they often weigh considerably more than standard polyurethane mattresses.
It is therefore necessary to turn them around more frequently.
If the central canals are not properly aired and above, they are on a firm basis, they keep moisture inside. Moisture can even appear below.
When choosing a bed, customs also influence it.
Anyone who has spent a lot of time abroad often uses a very high mattress with a soft layer and will have trouble feeling good on a lower and hard surface.
"Almost every hockey player who came back from the NHL complained that they didn't sleep as well here."
"For his bruised shoulders, heels and hips needed mattresses with a soft viscoelastic layer."
"This type of mattresses are also recommended for people with diabetes that time nervous system problems, so they get poorly information from joints and skin," explains Sylva Hadamcziková, who specializes in padded furniture.
Many hockey players, like other customers, have long preferred viscoelastic mattresses.
"Today there is no problem, because they have these suitable Tempur and the Italian Magniflex, but also the Czech brand Tropico."
You don't have to be an NHL player anymore to appreciate viscoelastica.
This "miracle" works in a very simple way.
Optimizes your stiffness and shape depending on the heat absorbed or adapts to your body heat.
Nothing exerts pressure; during the night, it will not turn like after a hard match.
She just sleeps better.
Viscoelastics also works as a protection against sores.
When choosing the size of the mattress, add to its height the length of its feet, that is, between 21 and 34 cm.
A man or woman with a height of about 180 cm will need a bed between 210 and 220 cm.
The minimum width for a person should be, in a double room, 90 cm, in total 180 cm.
In the case of single rooms, for example single rooms, it is recommended at least between 120 and 140 cm.
So that a possible visit is also comfortable.
"If not, you can apply a simple rule to calculate width: when lying face up, you should have your hands comfortably shrunk towards your elbows," advises engineer Helena Prokopová, expert at Cechu čalouníků a dekoratérů, who has been working on the problem of healthy sleep and furniture ergonomics for many years, a subject taught in specialized schools.
In the double rooms, each one needs its own mattress and mattress, so during the purchase you have to pay attention to combine the height of the mattresses.
Otherwise, it will be necessary to mount the sommers at different heights, which is not always possible on all beds.
The foam mattresses should have a minimum height of 14 cm, the models with inside springs a minimum of 15 cm, of which at least three centimeters are for the layer that adapts to the shapes and softness.
"When you touch it with your hand or when you sit on the mattress, you should definitely not notice the springs," warns Helena Prokopová.
Each mattress requires a specific type of mattress.
The fully padded bedrooms, in which the mattress and the base are like Siamese, make no sense in the bedroom.
The mattresses breathe badly and you can't wash your case, which today is often done.
And since every night we sweat between 0.2 and 0.75 l of sweat, it is clear that after about five or seven years the mattress will start to remind us of a large (and congested) sieve.
For this reason, specialists reject slogans that speak of a mattress life of up to 25 years or even of a lifetime guarantee.
However, everything has a but.
For this reason, sellers give advice: in mattresses with a width of 120 or 140 cm, carefully take care of the cleaning and washing of the case, but better add a mattress protector that can be easily removed and washed.
Although zippered mattress covers are currently made throughout its perimeter, so when you open them in two parts (something very important for washing and the size of the washing machine!), handling them in larger models (and for one person only) when lifting the mattress may seem like a fight between a fly weight and a heavy weight.
In bed, instead of a sock, do you have a firm board?
Never!
At least a lot for the beds designed to spend one night visiting.
However, it should make (if you don't already have them) ventilation holes on the table and should be used with a mattress with springs inside and a minimum height of 15 cm with springs in bags (such as the German Taschenfederkern) and a soft layer.
Polyurethane mattresses should not be used on such bases.
For non-jointable sheet sommers containing between 14 and 18 sheets, latex mattresses or sandwich mattresses (e.g. a combination of latex and coconut fibre) may be used, although it is always better to have a sommer with a greater number of sheets, 28 or more, in which the sheets of the lumbar zone are reinforced and their rigidity can be regulated.
Articulated sheet sommers should not be used with a spring mattress, as they do not react to reclination.
In addition to adjusting the stiffness of the blades, shoulder protection can also be used.
This is a special fastening of the sheets that allows you to press or even tilt the sheets in such a way that they "wrap" perfectly to your shoulders during sleep.
For men with very wide shoulders, this is something very important.
Even the manufacturers of mattresses who, in the "male", began to use a softer area just around the shoulders remember them.
They also remember women, for whom they put a softer area around the hips.
For the most demanding customers, there are somieres with cross structure or boards with so-called multitorsion damping.
The pressure is distributed between different points and the tension is lowered.
It should also be borne in mind that, even if you use the appropriate mattress and mattress, if you use a bad pillow (large and "mullid"), most of the advantages will disappear.
The basic rule is simple: the pillow must hold the head and the corners can only reach the shoulders, so that the muscles can be relaxed.
The appropriate size recommended is 50 x 60 cm, something normal for example in Scandinavia.
When lying on the side, the pillow should be at the same level (when combined with the sock with shoulder reinforcement or the softer area of the mattress) as the shoulder height.
Modern mattresses have something to do with, it seems, the original straw-filled mattresses.
Manufacturers continue to use, increasingly, natural materials or, at least, mixtures.
In fact, biological mattresses are fashionable.
Oil-based raw materials, which produce polyurethane foam, are filled with natural oils, e.g. castor or soy.
In fact, virtually all known manufacturers use soybeans.
"Biological, in the case of mattresses, means that the center is made only of materials of natural origin," explains Petr Vašíček of the company Tropico Plus.
Natural substances are also used during the manufacture of the mattress cover, one of the first aloe vera.
But you can also choose the microcapsules, which release a fresh aroma to forest or lavender.
There are also differences for men and women.
While men "refresh" with brise vegetable extracts, so that the mattress bottom absorbs heat and refreshes the body, women prefer to "heat" the bottom.
The red pepper extract improves blood circulation, so that women feel warmer.
The favourites today?
The mattresses made of cold foam, which are more porous, with an adapted cell structure, which makes them more permeable than those of normal polyurethane and offer more permeability.
The combination of various rigidities of cold foam and viscoelastic allows to manufacture mattresses of various areas that know perfectly where the head, shoulders and heels go.
A good quality mattress will cost you seven thousand crowns up.
Those who perform a therapeutic function usually have lower VAT, since they are considered as health means.
The first to gain this advantage in the Czech Republic was Gumotex.
