"Pakistan has had to hire personnel with strict religious beliefs to protect nuclear installations; given the fall in educational and cultural levels, extremist organizations have more opportunities to recruit people working on nuclear or missile programs," said expert Yuri Korolev of the Russian Foreign Ministry at a meeting with his American counterparts.
